The paper deals with the language recognition power of quantum Turing machines and quantum finite automata, which are topics related to computational complexity theory and quantum computing. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.QL (Quantum Physics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the space bounds of these machines, which relates to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper introduces a new QTM model, which could potentially fall under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
